<br>
Well I hate to post this here because I just know it will end up getting nerfed if I do.<br>
<br>
The MS3 pet has a rare chance of holding its own with an epic.<br>
<br>
In my experience one in 15 MS3 pets will hit for 60 and have a DS.<br>
<br>
HOW?  you might ask.<br>
<br>
Well If you get a MAX MS3 summoning that has a DS (50 point DS that the Decoy pet has) then you have a pet that will come out almost even to an EPIC.<br>
<br>
The MS3 pet will if it is of that pet type cast a DS on itself but it won't cast any spells, VI nerfed them so they would proc offensive spells however in the process of nerfing the pets do not have high dex do they do not proc anything.<br>
<br>
The MS3 pet since it does not cast will melee 2 times as much as a normal pet.<br>
<br>
The addiitonal melee and the 50 pt DS give it the power it needs to challange the mage epic.<br>
<br>
Against MOBs the MS3/DS pet will do about as well as EPIC as long as your in a group.  The epic has powerful spells and stuns so it has an edge.<br>
<br>
In PVP MS3/DS vrs Epic I have seen MS3 win 1 out of 4 fights.<br>
The ones it lost the Epic was under 20 percent health.<br>
<br>
If your on Saryrn and want to setup a friendly challange send me a tell.  Unless things have changed since I last tested it these are my findings.<br>
<br>
No, its not an epic replacement.  But you have around 1 in 15 chance of getting a pet that is for all practical purposes 80 percent as good for exp group fighting.<br>
<br>
Since it is a level 60 spell however... the point is kindof moot unless yoru doing the alternitive skills.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rthen Majere<br>
Arch Mage<br>
